{"word":"H5216 - נִיר - nîyr - neer - Candle","slug":"H5216","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">נִיר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>nîyr"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>neer"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Candle"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E0;&#x05E8;&#x05D4;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05E0;&#x05E8;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05E0;&#x05D9;&#x05E8;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05E0;&#x05E8;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05E0;&#x05D9;&#x05E8; - n&#x0131;&#x0302;yr  nir  ne&#x0302;yr  ne&#x0302;r  ne&#x0302;ra&#x0302;h</b> - <i>neer, neer, nare, nare, nay-raw'</i><p/>From a primitive root (see <a href=\"#/H5214\">H5214</a> and <a href=\"#/H5135\">H5135</a>) properly meaning to <i>glisten</i>; a <i>lamp</i> (that is, the burner) or <i>light</i> (literally or figuratively): - candle, lamp, light."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4501\">H4501</a>, <a href=\"#/H5369\">H5369</a>, <a href=\"#/H5374\">H5374</a>"}]}